hugh shelton  wikipedia hugh shelton from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search h hugh shelton general henry h shelton us army born  january   age  tarboro north carolina allegiance united states of america servicebranch united states army rank general commands held chairman joint chiefs of staff special operations command xviii airborne corps nd airborne division battleswars vietnam war gulf war operation uphold democracy awards defense distinguished service medal  army distinguished service medal  bronze star  with v device combat infantryman badge military free fall parachutist badge special forces tab ranger tab congressional gold medal other work chairman board of directors red hat corporation director anheuser busch director anteon international director protective products of america ppato general henry hugh shelton born january   is a retired american career military officer of the united states army he served as chairman of the joint chiefs of staff from  to  contents  early life family and education  military service  postmilitary career  quotes  decorations and badges  references  external links early life family and educationedit born in tarboro north carolina shelton was raised just outside the small town of speed north carolina north carolina highway  which runs through speed to hobgood north carolina right past the homestead he was raised on was later named general henry hugh shelton hwy in his honor shelton attended north carolina state university and was a member of pershing rifles he earned a bachelor of science degree in textile engineering while earning his army commission through rotc training sheltons further education includes a master of science degree in political science from auburn university at montgomery in  as well as studies at the air command and staff college and the national war college shelton married carolyn l johnson in  and have three sons together in  he underwent spinal surgery military serviceedit shelton served two tours of duty in vietnam with the th special forces group and with the rd airborne brigade followed by a series of command and staff assignments following the gulf war shelton commanded the nd airborne division at fort bragg in his home state of north carolina in  he was given command of xviii airborne corps shelton led the joint task force responsible for operation uphold democracy in haiti in  in  shelton a special forces soldier was promoted to the rank of general and the position of commander in chief of united states special operations command socom he was the first graduate of the us army special forces program to command united states special operations command upon the retirement of john m shalikashvili shelton was appointed chairman of the joint chiefs of staff on october   shelton led the planning of the kosovo war in  during his time in office later during his time in that office he coined the phrase dover test testing the support for a war based on the reaction of the people after seeing american casualties returning at the dover air force base during the events of september   shelton was on a plane traveling to a nato meeting in europe but turned back and returned to washington upon sheltons end of term president george w bush nominated thenvice chairman air force general richard myers who was sworn in on october   postmilitary careeredit in  shelton founded the general hugh shelton leadership center at north carolina state university the center was created to inspire educate and develop valuesbased leaders both locally and globally committed to personal integrity professional ethics and selfless service in his retirement shelton joined the board of directors of red hat corporation in april  and was elected that boards chairman in  he also holds directorships at anheuser busch anteon international and protective products of america ppato at his alma mater of north carolina state university the general hugh shelton leadership center was founded in  and grants scholarships to young men and women whom are committed to personal integrity professional ethics and selfless service shelton also served as an advisor to senator john edwards presidential campaign from  shelton created a minor controversy for  democratic presidential candidate retired us army general wesley clark a subordinate to shelton during the  kosovo military actions when he stated i will tell you the reason clark came out of europe early had to do with integrity and character issues things that are very near and dear to my heart … ill just say wes wont get my vote casting doubt upon the presidential contenders legitimacy on march   general shelton announced his endorsement of senator hillary clinton for the  democratic presidential primary stating i’ve been with senator clinton when she has been with our military men and women i know from those experiences that she understands the demands and sacrifice of military life i am confident she will always put the readiness and well being of our troops first she is ready to be commanderinchief general shelton was the second chairman of the joint chiefs of staff to endorse senator clinton the first being general john shalikashvili on october   general shelton published his autobiography without hesitation the odyssey of an american warrior along with coauthors ron levinson and malcolm mcconnell an excerpt tells the story of a highranking clinton cabinet member proposing that general shelton intentionally allow an american pilot to be killed by the iraqis to have an excuse to retaliate and go to war the book also tells of bill clintons tearful confession to general shelton a time during the clinton administration when a close clinton aide lost possession of the biscuit top secret presidential nuclear launch authorization codes details of a contentious camp david meeting among president george w bush and his national security council immediately after  where internal battle lines were drawn his book also says there were multiple attempts to kill osama bin laden that were shot down by madeleine albright on august   a statue of general shelton was unveiled and dedicated at the airborne special operations museum in fayetteville nc the statue was commissioned and donated by h ross perot on october   general shelton appeared on this week with christiane amanpour on december   appeared on the daily show with jon stewart and on december   appeared on the charlie rose show on pbs and bloomberg tv to promote the publication of his memoir without hesitation the odyssey of an american warrior on october   general shelton was honored at the th annual brian  kendras bluegrass party in speed nc he was presented with a distinguished achievements plaque and a road side display at the entrance of speed nc honoring general sheltons home town and acknowledgement of his achievements shelton and his wife carolyn j shelton established the hugh and carolyn shelton military neurotrauma foundation in  to fund research into traumatic brain injury among military personnel quotesedit warning that even fort bragg could be harmed by budget cuts hugh shelton stated doing more with less is great for sissies and cowards standing up for whats right is what great leaders do decorations and badgesedit general shelton has been decorated for service to include badge combat infantryman badge badge master parachutist badge badge special forces tab ranger tab st row awards defense distinguished service medal w  oak leaf clusters distinguished service medal w  oak leaf clusters nd row awards legion of merit w  oak leaf clusters bronze star w valor device   oak leaf clusters purple heart meritorious service medal w  oak leaf clusters rd row awards air medal w  device army commendation medal w  oak leaf clusters national defense service medal w  service stars armed forces expeditionary medal th row awards vietnam service medal w  bronze service star southwest asia service medal w  service stars army service ribbon army overseas service ribbon th row awards vietnam gallantry cross w bronze star vietnam campaign medal kuwait liberation medal saudi arabia kuwait liberation medal badge pathfinder badge military free fall parachute badge badge office of the joint chiefs of staff identification badge air assault badge badge navy and marine corps parachutist insignia german parachutist badge in bronze unit awards us army presidential unit citation us navy presidential unit citation joint meritorious unit award unit awards meritorious unit commendation vietnam gallantry cross unit citation vietnam civil actions medal unit citation referencesedit  a b c d e f g biography of henry hugh shelton associated press the dispatch  retrieved  october    who did that sign say p  archived  july  at the wayback machine  a b stout david  man in the news henry hugh shelton general who sets pace ny times retrieved  october    a b c exjoint chiefs chair undergoes spinal surgery cnn  retrieved  october    stout david  pg  time to take the dover test cnn  retrieved  october    larry king live httpwwwpatriotresourcecomwtcfederalsheltonhtml  cnn  missing or empty series help accessdate requires url help  general hugh shelton elected chairman of red hat board of directors red hat inc  august  retrieved  august    alan m wolf  august  red hat names gen shelton as chairman news  observer raleigh retrieved  august    httpsheltonleadershipncsueduabout  a b arkin william  the general unease with wesley clark la times retrieved  october    los altos town crier  gen shelton shocks celebrity forum says he wont support clark for president losaltosonlinecom  retrieved  december    httpwwwhillaryclintoncomnewsreleaseviewid  general hugh shelton  news hughsheltoncom  retrieved  december    httpwwwsaloncomnewspoliticswarroomclintonofficialiraqhughshelton  bill clinton wept over the monica lewinsky scandal  washington whispers usnewscom politicsusnewscom  retrieved  december    lauren frayer contributor  gene