as media related to hugh shelton army biography and career summary military offices preceded byjohn shalikashvili chairman of the joint chiefs of staff– succeeded byrichard myers vte chairmen of the joint chiefs of staff bradley radford twining lemnitzer taylor wheeler moorer brown jones vessey crowe powell jeremiah acting shalikashvili shelton myers pace mullen dempsey this page uses creative commons licensed content from wikipedia view authors retrieved from httpmilitarywikiacomwikihughsheltonoldid ad blocker interference detected wikia is a freetouse site that makes money from advertising we have a modified experience for viewers using ad blockers wikia is not accessible if you’ve made further modifications remove the custom ad blocker rules and the page will load as expected got sdcc sdcc guide star wars sdcc about general shelton  shelton leadership center about give resources contact shelton leadership center search for about general shelton to hear a talk from general shelton on political and military challenges during presidential transitions  to listen click here general henry hugh shelton usa r th chairman joint chiefs of staff center founder and executive director general henry h shelton was born in tarboro north carolina he received a bachelor’s degree in textiles from north carolina state university and was commissioned as a second lieutenant in the infantry through the reserve officer training corps general shelton spent the next  years in a variety of command and staff positions in the continental united states hawaii and vietnam he served two combat tours in vietnam the first with the th special forces group and the second with the rd airborne brigade also he commanded the d battalion th infantry in the th infantry division at fort lewis washington served as the th infantry division’s chief of staff for operations commanded the st brigade of the nd airborne division at fort bragg north carolina and was the chief of staff of the th mountain division at fort drum new york selected for promotion to brigadier general in  general shelton served two years in the operations directorate of the joint staff in  he began a twoyear assignment as the assistant division commander for operations of the st airborne division air assault at fort campbell kentucky where he participated in the liberation of kuwait during operation desert shieldstorm after the gulf war general shelton was promoted to major general and assumed command of the nd airborne division fort bragg north carolina in  he was promoted to lieutenant general and assumed command of the xviii airborne corps in  during his tenure as corps commander general shelton led the united states joint task force that restored democracy in haiti in march  he was promoted to general and became commander in chief of the us special operations command general shelton became the th chairman of the joint chiefs of staff on october   and served two twoyear terms retiring on september   throughout his tenure as chairman us forces were in heavy demand and participated in numerous joint operations around the globe during his tenure general shelton worked tirelessly on behalf of service members their families and military retirees by championing a number of landmark quality of life initiatives including the largest military pay raise in  years pay table and bonus reform and critical improvements in both retirement and healthcare programs he made great strides in improving the readiness and retention of the current force while simultaneously crafting joint vision the roadmap for the future joint force general shelton established joint forces command to consolidate joint experimentation efforts and guide the transformation of the us armed forces for the st century general shelton holds a master’s degree from auburn university and has attended harvard university the air command and staff college and the national war college among his many military awards general shelton has received four defense distinguished service medals two army distinguished service medals the legion of merit the bronze star medal for valor and the purple heart he has been decorated by  foreign governments and in  general shelton was knighted by queen elizabeth ii highlights of his civilian awards include the charlotte nc world affairs council world citizen award for  north carolina’s highest award for public service the eisenhower award from the business executives for national security the american academy of achievement’s golden plate award intrepid freedom award and recognition as national father of the year among others for his exemplary service to his country the th congress bestowed the congressional gold medal on general shelton on september   general shelton is the  recipient of the united states army infantry’s doughboy award and the  nfl and college football hall of fame distinguished american award he was also presented the army special operations professionals man of the year award in  after retiring from the armed forces general shelton served as president international operations mic industries from  he has also served as a director on a number of public company boards to include anheuser busch companies  anteon international  and professional products of america  he is currently chairman of the board of red hat inc and serves as a director of l communications  in addition he serves as a director for the following private companies  covant at solutions robbinsgioia the o’gara group professional products enterprises and highmark he previously served as a director of biosignia and professional products services ps general shelton is also the executive director of the general hugh shelton leadership center at north carolina state university and serves as director of the hugh and carolyn shelton military neurotrauma foundation washington dc in  his book” secrets of success valuesbased leaders” was released and his autobiography “without hesitation” was released in october  general shelton report an accessibility barrier the department for disability support services menu search apply give jobs maps directory   office of innovation and economic development home willis building reservations research economic development and engagement volunteer and service learning center about us staff directory directions our priorities who we serve economic development professionals town planners local officials legislators community leaders faculty staff student and alumni k educators entrepreneurs and industry leaders citizens and visitors nonprofit professionals constituent units community and regional development industry and economic development center for survey research ecus entrepreneurial initiative office of technology transfer small business and technology development center oeied outreach services center for municipal management and innovation innovation design lab ecus outreach network chancellors innovation workforce initiative engagement and outreach scholars academy middle school innovators academy shelton leadership challenge  ecu champions of freedom case studies sustainable tourism arise revolving education around partnership tillery wellness program barracks of the future noncredit training news what is the challenge challenge registration sponsorship opportunities serve on the staff financial scholarships general shelton general shelton general henry hugh shelton usa r th chairman joint chiefs of staff ncsu shelton leadership center founder and executive director general henry h shelton is originally from speed north carolina a town near tarboro in eastern north carolina he received a bachelors degree in textiles from north carolina state university and was commissioned as a second lieutenant in the infantry through the reserve officer training corps    general shelton spent the next  years in a variety of command and staff positions in the continental united states hawaii and vietnam he served two combat tours in vietnam the first with the th special forces group and the second with the rd airborne brigade also he commanded the d battalion th infantry in the th infantry division at fort lewis washington served as the th infantry divisions chief of staff for operations commanded the st brigade of the nd airborne division at fort bragg north carolina and was the chief of staff of the th mountain division at fort drum new york selected for promotion to brigadier general in  general shelton served two years in the operations directorate of the joint staff in  he began a twoyear assignment as the assistant division commander for operations of the st airborne division air assault at fort campbell kentucky where he participated in the liberation of kuwait during operation desert shieldstorm after the gulf war general shelton was promoted to major general and assumed command of the nd airborne division fort bragg north carolina in  he was promoted to lieutenant general and assumed command of the xviii airborne corps in  during his tenure as corps commander general shelton led the united states joint task force that restored democracy in haiti in march  he was promoted to general and became commander in chief of the us special operations command general shelton became the th chairman of the joint chiefs of staff on october   and served two twoyear terms retiring on september   throughout his tenure as chairman us forces were in heavy demand and participated in numerous joint operations around the globe during his tenure general shelton worked tirelessly on behalf of service members their families and military retirees by championing a number of landmark quality of life initiatives including the largest military pay raise in  years pay table and bonus reform and critical improvements in both retirement and healthcare programs he made great strides in improving the readiness and retention of the current force while simultaneously crafting joint vision the roadmap for the future joint force general shelton established joint forces command to consolidate joint experimentation efforts and guide the transformation of the us armed forces for the st century general shelton holds a masters degree from auburn university and has attended harvard university the air command and staff college and the national war college  among his many military awards general shelton has received four defense distinguished service medals two army distinguished service medals the legion of merit the bronze star medal for valor and the purple heart he has been decorated by  foreign governments and in  general shelton was knighted by queen elizabeth ii highlights of his civilian awards include the charlotte nc world affairs council world citizen award for  north carolinas highest award for public service the eisenhower award from the business executives for national security the american academy of achievements golden plate award intrepid freedom award and recognition as national father of the year among others for his exemplary service to his country the th congress bestowed the congressional gold medal on general shelton on september     general shelton is the  recipient of the united states army infantry’s doughboy award and the  nfl and college football hall of fame distinguished american award he was also presented the army special operations professionals man of the year award in  after retiring from the armed forces general shelton served as president international operations mic industries from  he has also served as a director on a number of public company boards to include anheuser busch companies  anteon international  and professional products of america  he is currently chairman of the board of red hat inc and serves as a director of l communications  in addition he serves as a director for the following private companies  covant at solutions robbinsgioia the o’gara group professional products enterprises and highmark he previously served as a director of biosignia and pro