st with the th special forces group and the second with the rd airborne brigade also he commanded the d battalion th infantry in the th infantry division at fort lewis washington served as the th infantry division’s chief of staff for operations commanded the st brigade of the nd airborne division at fort bragg north carolina and was the chief of staff of the th mountain division at fort drum new york   selected for promotion to brigadier general in  general shelton served two years in the operations directorate of the joint staff in  he began a twoyear assignment as the assistant division commander for operations of the st airborne division air assault at fort campbell kentucky where he participated in the liberation of kuwait during operation desert shieldstorm after the gulf war he was promoted to major general and assumed command of the nd airborne division fort bragg north carolina in  he was promoted to lieutenant general and assumed command of the xviii airborne corps in  during his tenure as corps commander general shelton led the united states joint task force that restored democracy in haiti in march  he was promoted to general and became commander in chief of the us special operations command   general shelton became the th chairman of the joint chiefs of staff on october   and served  twoyear terms retiring on september   in this capacity he was the principle military advisor to presidents clinton and bush as well as the secretaries of defense and the national security council   among his many military awards general shelton has received four defense distinguished service medals two army distinguished service medals the legion of merit the bronze star medal for valor and the purple heart   for his exemplary service to his country the th congress bestowed the congressional gold medal on general shelton on september   he has also been decorated by  foreign governments and in  general shelton was knighted by queen elizabeth ii   general shelton is the  recipient of the united states army infantry’s doughboy award and the  nfl and college football hall of fame distinguished american award he was also presented the army special operations professionals man of the year award in    highlights of his civilian awards include the charlotte nc world affairs council world citizen award for  north carolina’s highest award for public service the eisenhower award from the business executives for national security the american academy of achievement’s golden plate award intrepid freedom award and recognition as national father of the year among others   after retiring from the armed forces general shelton served as president international operations mic industries from  he has also served as a director on a number of public company boards to include anheuser busch companies  anteon international  and professional products of america  he is currently chairman of the board of red hat inc and serves as a director of l communications  in addition he serves on boards of the following private companies  covant at solutions the o’gara group point blank enterprises and highmark he previously served as a director of robbinsgioia biosignia and professional products services ps general shelton is the executive director of the general hugh shelton leadership center at north carolina state university and serves as a director of the hugh and carolyn shelton military neurotrauma foundation washington dc   general shelton has authored two books “secrets of success valuesbased leaders” was published in  and his autobiography “without hesitation” was released in october  back to about us   point blank enterprises inc company home about us executive leadership history partners commitment online store careers products point blank body armor paraclete paca protective products enterprises the protective group advanced technology group first tactical gould  goodrich support where to buy news press releases events resources site map warranty register you